The paper deals with the communication of information through porous media, which involves the use of statistical breakthrough curves and computational fluid dynamics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the use of numerical simulations and modeling techniques indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) and Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS) sub-categories. The study of porous media and its impact on communication performance may also be relevant to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. Finally, the use of breakthrough curves to analyze the data suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category.
